reviews: Overall our stay here was above standards. I highly recommend this place to anyone that’s going to Paris, you’ll be at the center of all main attractions, the amenities are fantastic here. We'll be back for our next visit. If you are lucky enough you’ll meet with Yassine as you arrive in the hotel, he’s the person that accommodated our transition upon arrival and departure is. He provided high quality services, making our stay very comfortable.

We had a wonderful experience at Renaissance Vendome. I am always nervous checking in to a European hotel because you never know what you are going to get. And when we first checked in to the hotel and entered our room, we were very disappointed with the size of the room. We couldn't even unpack our things. However, we spoke with Yana at the front desk, who was so kind, professional, and wonderful. She showed me another room, but offered the largest room in our category which would be available the following day. We moved to the larger room (316) on the second day of our stay and it was perfect - clean, spacious, comfortable. Yana continued to be wonderful throughout our stay, always checking in with me to be sure everything was okay, and always with a smile and a gentle warmth. The rest of the staff was great too. Everybody was very friendly, helpful, and there was a sense that they were there to serve the guests and make their stay as comfortable as possible. The hotel is located in a perfect location, in the First Arrondissement, on a side street, a bit away from the tourist chaos. We walked everywhere - to the museums, to the 6th for dinner every night, to shopping. If you don't mind walking, it's a perfect location. The breakfast in the morning was fine, nothing special, but did the job. We enjoyed dinner at nearby Flotte several times. While all of the local hotels send their guests there, it's actually very good. We loved sitting at the bar (91) in a secluded side spot for just the two of us. The only negative thing I can say about the hotel is that they are not very generous with towels, and forget about getting washcloths. However, when I called down every night for more towels, they always brought more up right away. If you are looking for a Ritz or Four Seasons, this is not the hotel for you. But, if you are looking for a nice hotel that does the job well, Renaissance Vendome is great. My husband and I both agree that we would stay again. It was just easy. And again, thank you Yana, and the rest of the staff for making our stay so enjoyable.

Merci Bien to the whole team at Renaissance Paris Vendome! We had such a wonderful stay with our extended family (2 couples & 4 kids ranging from age 7 to 12). We were a little apprehensive following some of the previous reviews, but we should not have been worried - it was a perfect base for us and we were SO well looked after. Paris is so expensive these days and the Renaissance isn't cheap but is definitely great value.

Staff - AMAZING - so friendly and welcoming, our only tip is to make sure you have lots of small bills as you'll want to tip everyone continuously. From topping up our glasses at the free happy hour to giving our kids bottles of water to insisting we take one of their umbrellas with us on our return to the Eurostar 'in case it rains on your way' - we were blown away by their attentiveness.

Family appropriateness - our kids felt totally welcome; extra beds with extra towels, robes, slippers were all ready on check-in; the pool was perfect for post-touring breaks - not big but ideal for splashing around playing Marco Polo.

Rooms - simple but stylish; we weren't crazy about the photos on the ceilings but the beds were super comfortable, nice coffee facilities, and great water pressure in the bathrooms. I think our rooms were called Prestige - bathrooms were huge (some reviews have noted they are a little dated - true but no big deal). We had rooms 512, 514 and 515 which were all at the end of a hallway together; this set-up was ideal for us (and exactly what I'd asked the Marriott team for - thanks again!).

Amenities - so impressed by the extra values on offer, including welcome drinks, a tea and pastry station in the morning, and a complimentary happy hour cocktail on offer daily from 5-6pm; the restaurant wasn't operating, but room service was available and there are so many places to eat nearby.

Location - ideal for all the main sights - super close to the Louvre, Opera, walkable to the Champs Elysees, with a Metro station a 3 minute walk away and so much on the doorstep from a Carrefour minimart around the corner for snacks to Cafe Kitsune for coffee, pastry shops aplenty and of course ever-popular Angelina (though the queue was too long for us to wait this time).

Thanks again to the whole team - see you next time!

We stayed here for three nights before departing France after a week in Strasbourg. We have previously stayed at different Marriot properties several times, including the nearby Westin, in the Vendom area. We were excited to try the Renaissance based on the positive reviews.

We were delighted to be greeted by such a warm front desk/reception team, and the welcome beverages were a nice touch. The lobby is very impressive - beautiful, modern, clean. We also very much appreciated the staff's welcome gifts in our room (balloons, champagne, and desserts galore)!

The room, in general, however, was just fine (certainly better than the Westin's rooms), and the bed/pillows were very comfortable. However, the bathroom was showing its wear, and we did not feel showering in the shower, which had mold in the ceilings and drain.

The location, of course, is outstanding - which is why we favor the Vendome area.

All in all, for the price, we expected more and were a bit disappointed. We continue to be disappointed with Marriott's offerings in Paris.

But special thank you to the staff, especially the front door staff who went out of their way to learn our names and engage in conversation daily.

Big shout out to Yassine( doorman) who went out of his way. Great guy and amazing service.

The hotel is good standard, but bathroom is a big let down. The shower are too low, and for a 5 star hotel I would expect much better amenities in the bathroom. Rooms are small considering I paid £600 a night.

It's always so sad when a beautiful hotel in a great location for designer shopping (mostly that is why you would stay here) has a HUGE LACK OF HOUSEKEEPING STAFF !
There was a pen on the floor right near one night table and it never was picked up!
You don't need excuses from the hotel. You need to find a hotel that cares about housekeeping and has someone recheck each room ... there should ALWAYS be a hotel checklist for housekeeping. This is supposed to be a 4-5 star hotel and it IS NOT

Beautiful small boutique style hotel well located and connected to atracciones and restaurants. Attention of staff en terms outstanding, with one exception.
Just enjoyed the relaxing atmosphere and stylish design. Would come back anytime.

We stayed at the Renaissance in January, great location to walk to many things. The hotel staff was very friendly and accommodating. There are croissants and coffee/tea/juice for breakfast or you can purchase breakfast. We had 3 people in the twin prestige room, there was a 3rd comfortable bed brought into the room. The room was tight for 3 people but it was fine as we were only there a few nights and out most of the day visiting the city. We stayed on the 4th floor courtyard side and the room was very quiet.

Great hotel. Smaller and very focused on service.

1. The staff is fantastic. Very eager to please.
2. Excellent Concierge team. We worked mostly with Thomas who was a gem. He was quick on replying to our questions and gave honest advice. He helped us throughout our stay and even helped planned a Christmas morning gift surprise for our little boy.
3. Small heated indoor pool but nice they offer it. My little boy loved the shower in the pool area as the water shoots out from all angles.
4. Appreciated the turndown service.
5. Room was clean and well maintained. Needed some more storage but otherwise good.
6. Very good location by the high-end shopping.

Hope to return.

Thank you Thomas and team.

This hotel is a gem in Paris . Location superb, staff amazing and overall a great place to stay. The staff makes you feel very welcome.. In particular , Mattia and Samuel went out of their way during our stay to ensure that our every need was attended to. We got a great corner room (Parisian king). The hotel is steps away from everything. We barely used Ubers/taxis and were able to walk everywhere. There are so many good restaurants within steps of the hotel and staff was spot on in their recommendations.

A few notes for areas of improvement - breakfast at the adjoining restaurant was very crowded and hectic (we skipped most days) . .Gym is very damp and humid, not worth working out in.

I am a Marriott elite member and have always felt confident in booking their hotels. This particular venue clearly needs to be renovated; woodwork is scratched and broken. Despite their claims to the contrary, there is nothing luxurious about it. `The heating in one of the rooms did not work at all. The hallway carpets and walls are dingy. The furnishings are cheap and poorly constructed.. The floor in the gym seemed to have not been swept or mopped in a very long time. The locker facilities were cramped. The “spa” seemed non-existent; the area was so dirty I would not consider any treatments there. Do yourself a favor and look elsewhere.

I am unsure how this is a 5 star hotel. We booked the Studio Suite which was 3 levels up from a basic room and barely have any room to crawl out of the bed, let alone store any baggage. The room doesn’t even have a mini bar, the TV doesn’t work, there was no working hair dryer and the concierge couldn’t help with any lunch, dinner or show tickets. I would not recommend spending your money here. I have stayed at Fairfield Inn and Suites in the United States that are nicer.

The service, location, food and room were all lovely. The steam, sauna and hammam were heavenly.
This is close to Louvre, shopping (all the best shopping) and more.
Tunde was a very amazing resource and so friendly.
I will be back!!

FAMILY OF 4 WITH 2 SMALL CHILDREN

NO FRONT DOOR HELP
First red flag, when we were dropped off at the hotel, there was no one at the front door to help us with our bags. I was surprised considering this is listed as a 5 star hotel.

NO UPGRADE.
We booked the hotel through Amex Travel and it was part of the Hotel Collection, which entitles to an upgrade and 100$ hotel credit. Also, my husband is Marriott Bonvoy gold, which entitles to upgrades when available as well, yet none was offered. I wasn’t upset since it is a small hotel, but the associate insisted I did my booking through Expedia when I didn’t and I had the print outs. For reference, I had the same “double upgrade” available at the Gritti palace in Venice and they honored the double upgrade and gave us an apartment.

ROOM READY AT 5pm
Check in at the hotel is at 4p. We got to Paris early so we left our bags and checked in at 9:30am. We were told our room was being prepared and someone would text when it was ready. We went to see the city, have lunch, ect. We arrived to the hotel at 3:30pm thinking our room should be ready soon. We were told it was still being prepared. At 4:15 my husband inquired about the status of the room and was told the prior guests were granted a late checkout and it was being cleaned now. We didn’t get our keys until 5pm. I was with my 2 children, who were asleep in the couches in the lobby.

FAILED TO ARRANGE TAXI FOR DEPARTURE
Our last night, we arranged with the front desk a taxi for our departure the next day. Since we are a family of 4 with a lot of luggage, we wanted to ensure a larger car was available. They wrote our information on a notebook and said the taxi would be there at 9am. On the day of our departure at 9:15 am my husband inquires regarding the status of the taxi. He is told there is no taxi scheduled and that there is a marathon that morning and all streets are closed, therefore none will be available. They did not offer any assistance. My husband and I had to arrange 2 separate Ubers and barely made it to our flight.

We have travelled internationally as a family to Spain, Greece, Austria, and France. NEVER have we encountered such lack of concern or helpfulness from hotel staff. We were utterly disappointed, particularly since this hotel is part of the Amex Hotel Collection and we are Marriott Bonvoy Gold as well. I would avoid at all costs.

The best feature is that it’s within walking distance of many of the important sites in Paris.
The lobby is very spacious and beautifully decorated, a welcoming place for guests to gather.
Yana in reception greeted us warmly upon arrival. Nickson was a jewel and delightful who was very helpful in getting us settled into our rooms.
Marie-Paule was also extremely helpful in organizing our time in Paris❤️,
The entire staff went above and beyond to make our 3 nights very special.
Highly recommend staying here on your next trip to Paris.

Started staying at this property soon after it converted to a Marriott in 2005/6. It is wonderfully located in the 1st near the Louvre and Place Vendome.
When it first opened it had all the charm of a boutique Parisian Hotel. Gracious staff, clean well appointed rooms; along with nice welcoming gifts and exceptional toiletries; plus local chocolates on your pillow at night.
From 2006 to now it has evolved from being unique to an chain hotel with little charm and a loud bar that is open till the early hours of the morning on weekends. Pity those folks on the bottom floors.
The local chocolate has become a piece of penny taffy and the toiletries are now bottles on the wall of the shower as you usually see at your local Courtyard Marriott. Amazingly, if you book with points, which I did for part of my stay, the rates are some of the highest in Paris.
The rooms see like they are showing signs of wear, even though hotel has recently been remodeled. Leaking shower, toilet that ran, burned out lights, dirt under the bed. Not what you would expect from a hotel charging $800 + per night on the nights that were paid for.
This is no reflection on the staff, which is very accommodating. The breakfast was excellent and as I said, location is great. Sadly it has lost its charm and, probably, me as a future guest.
Just as FYI, I am a loyal Lifetime Marriot Titanium member.

I wanted a special hotel to celebrate my wife Birthday and this was perfect. It is a lovely hotel in a fantastic location for designer shopping. It also has a spa with a great indoor pool in the basement, which was a plus for me. It has a very small funky bar with cool music and an incredible restaurant (Balagan) attached which you simply must visit for dinner, but book in advance. The staff are all very helpful but if you want a taxi back to the airport you should book through reception and not the bell boy because we ended up paying more that we should have due to that mistake.

Centrally located only minutes from the Louvre and Tuileries gardens. We had a family suite which was spacious for 4 adults to stay. The bathroom was large and room was larger than expected. The breakfast was wonderful and the restaurant on the ground floor was one of the best restaurants we had experienced. The only negative is that we were on the 2nd floor right above the restaurant that played very loud music until about 1AM each night. Otherwise, highly recommend and would stay again but ask for a higher floor.

Our room was great, spacious and comfortable for our family of 4. We had a “family suite” so it was 2 connected rooms. The staff was helpful and spoke enough English to be able to help us. They gave a great recommendation for a kid friendly restaurant which was awesome. Great location close to the louvre and the Tuileries gardens. Everyone was very friendly and were a huge help making sure we got to the train station on time on a busy Monday morning.

We stayed at this property about 10 years ago and really enjoyed it. Wish I could say the same for our most recent visit.

On the positive side, the location is good. Near the Louvre. Check in was very easy and the desk staff was very nice. Things went downhill from there. When we went to our room in the afternoon, there were trays of food outside many other rooms. The next morning, the same trays were still there. It was disgusting. The bathroom door would not shut. We noticed it was held together with duct tape. REALLY!! The windows were not sealed well, and unfortunatley our room was above the front entrance to the hotel. People were mingling and smoking below our room well after midnight. It was very loud. The rooms are rather small and dark. The bathrooms are a good size though. Perhaps because we used points to pay for the room, we were given a worse location.

Finally, we requested a taxi for the airport, but when we went down at the appointed time,there was no taxi. One of the hotel staff had to run down the street and get us one, which took about 15 minutes. When I inquired as to what happened, the front desk person said the taxi they ordered came early and left. Couldn't they have called us to come down.

Perhaps because we used points to pay for the room, we were given a worse location.
However, I would not stay at this hotel again.

First, the location is great and the on site restaurant is a must.
However, very small king size rooms make accommodations for two with luggage very difficult.
Room service comes from the restaurant on site but you need to call reception and they order for you. Something as simple as coffee and croissants can take upwards of 40 minutes and only arrive because you have to call a second time. This happened 3 times.
Housekeeping needs to pay attention to things like empty water bottles in the room. We had eventually had 7 just to see if they would be thrown away but they were just left there on the table. Funny enough, water was not always provided when the room was straightened up so we had to ask the front desk for it. We also ran out of bath gel and hair conditioner that is supplied by the hotel. This is something that should be checked daily.
The elevator ended up being out of service -which happens. But before it was deemed out of order, I smelled sewage which they tried to cover up with very strong air freshener. Come to think of it, this may have been from the toilets being closed. One of the rooms on the street level was provided for bathroom use. Unfortunate for this to happen when the hotel was completely booked.
In addition, the wifi was constantly going on and off.
Marriott can do better.

In my opinion a number of these reviews are a bit harsh. Yes the rooms are not overly big but you do not come to Paris to spend lots of time in your room. The great upside is the unbeatable location. The major attractions are all walkable. The staff could not have been more friendly and helpful. We will return to Paris and we will stay at the Renaissance Paris Vendome Hotel again.

A lavish lifestyle boutique hotel in the heart of downtown Paris. Great location, Great Bed, rooms are rather small, understaffed and certain rooms the air-conditioning wasn't working (the house keeping provided a portable cooling fan like in the room, wasn't expecting this for a 4-star rated hotel, immediately requested for a change of room)

💫 🇫🇷 Thank you @renaissancevendome for making our recent stay with you so special. 🥰⁣
⁣
This is a lovely, newly renovated hotel, and the staff goes beyond expectations to ensure your stay is perfect.⁣
The location is excellent and within walking distance of all the main sites in Paris…. not forgetting the beautiful swimming pool, hotel spa and there is even a sauna and hammam area. ⁣
Ps loved the breakfast eggs!!
⁣
My family and I had such a wonderful stay at this hotel. ⁣
The hotel is child friendly and the staff always went the extra mile to ensure everyone felt welcome. They were so kind and attentive, they even joined in celebrations for our Dad’s 70th birthday 🥳 (We must say a special thank you to “Jussie” for making our stay that extra special) 🌹⁣
We truly had the most beautiful few days in Paris… 🌹⁣
Merci beaucoup ❤️🇫🇷⁣
⁣
⁣

Basically ok. Small rooms for 500 Euros. We could not access the hotel by car when we arrived as there was some disruptions, we had wifi not working for a day (with 2 teenage boys..), fitness room was not accessible for part of the stay, swimming pool is a big word, staff is ok (do not bother or distract them too much please… this is Paris…), breakfast is ok. Obviously location is fantastic. It was really a weird experience, we paid a lot for a palace experience and got a Courtyard experience…. An expensive joke… anyway, I still love Paris but in a different hotel next time.

Me and my wife booked this hotel for a week. The hotel is newly renovated and very clean.The location is excellent but the service is horrible. First we had to change rooms because next door to us there was a family with kids that would scream in the hallway until late at night and very early in the morning ( this is our first vacation away from our kids so we definitely didn’t want the screaming).
After moving the TV in the new room was not working properly we asked three times to have it fixed and so far nothing has been done.
Also, the turn down service is a hit or miss. Sometimes you get it .. sometimes you don’t… not what you expect for a 5 star hotel in the price range of this one.

This is a lovely hotel and the staff goes beyond expectations to make your stay more comfortable. My room wasn’t ready when I arrived. I was exhausted from my overnight flight and a horrendous delay at the airport where I had to stand in a crowd of people to get through customs for around one hour. I was so disappointed and mentioned that I wanted to take a shower so badly. I was offered use of one the showers in their spa. I had my own 2 room bathroom suit where I was able to open my suitcase, shower in privacy, and use a vanity. I felt like a new person!

After my sister arrived that afternoon, they sent us a complimentary bottle of wine to thank her for returning.

The room was small, but it was so comfortable and it overlooked a courtyard. The adjoining restaurant was perfect for breakfast, and the lobby was cozy enough to have drinks, after dinner.

And, of course, the location is perfect. We were blocks away from Place Vendome which was beautifully decked out for Christmas.

This was my first stay at this property, as the Westin, where I stayed earlier for one week, then left France for a day, was sold out for the nights following my return.

I stayed for years at the Westin Vendome, got a very nice suite facing the Tuileries on the 4th floor upgrade, although 5 of the nights were booked on points. That hotel earned my loyalty a long time ago by treating me very well with those suites with an incredible view.

I definitely knew that I would not get a view at the Renaissance, but, with a the SNAs that I had applied to my reservation and a discussion to the Front Desk Manager (the is no FOM and no DOR at this property, the last one being understandable in view of the size of the hotel). Two days prior to my arrival, there was still no reply on my SNA's request, which was very unusual. The FDM said that she would contact Marriott and one the next day, I received an email stating that my SNA request had been denied.

When I checked in in the evening, the Duty Manager, who tried to be helpful, told me that there was no suite or larger room available. He said that that there no message from his FDM, who had told me that she would try to find something for me, even if the SNAs were declined. He looked embarrassed but was not available to give me something better than a room that was 2 SQM larger than the one I booked. He told me that he would try to find something better for the following nights (I never heard from them again about this).
My reservation and my profile indicated a "High Floor" request, but I was assigned this small room on the 3rd floor / 2eme etage just above the entrance of the hotel, so I had the noise of the car doors closing when cars were dropping off or picking up guests at night time). My 3-night reservation was at an average of 650 euros per night (certainly the worst deal that I have got in my long guest "career".

On the next morning, on my way to breakfast, I saw the FDM who asked me how I was doing (no mention of the upgrade that did not happened). I told her that the only room of that size that I ever stayed at, in a hotel, was in Narita, where ANA booked me after a flight delay that made me miss my connection).
Having stayed at Starwood, then Marriott properties over 1,500 nights (with well over 1,400 in suites, following upgrades) since the programs started, I have seen (and talked many times to management people) about the training and way to handle customers, but did not recognize anything that this FDM told me that was fitting the Marriott's way. It was more like "If you want a suite or a large room, I would advise you to book what you prefer". She tried to educate me about small hotels (when I recently had nice suite upgrades at the Edition Barcelona, city that she is very familiar with, or the JW Marriott Bosphorus in Istanbul, both small hotels).

Apparently, this person (or the hotel) is not big on "Elite" recognition, as she did not bother to make any effort to offer me anything to somehow keep me at a certain level of happiness, which is what I have always experienced with Starwood or Marriott (but also with Hilton & IHG). No "Is there anything else that I could do to make your stay more comfortable or to keep you happy?" at this property (although I believe that it is included in Marriott's training).

Breakfast is at the hotel only restaurant. It is small and set up a little bit like The Pain Quotidien, with some large tables which can be shared. It is trying to have a very casual, home style, but that can be awkward.
On the first morning, when I got in, there was a guy standing next to a pole, making the pathway even more difficult, but I thought that he was a guest. It turned out that he was part of the staff, that did not bother to make things easier for the guests. This long curly hair guy had a shirt open almost up to his belly button - definitely another F&B standard. No exchange with him.
On the 2nd morning, it took him forever to bring me an espresso coffee. Just the order, followed by a thank you exchange with him.
On the 3rd morning, I was with my 84-year-old mother (with some asthma issue) and I was trying not to sit right next to other people, to make her feel more comfortable. A young trainee, that I had not seen during the previous mornings, was first insisting that we sat next to a couple when there were several larger tables available, but then let us seat at the table I was preferring. Problem easily resolved, but that previous mornings guy shows up and asked if there was an issue. I started to tell him that it was taken care of, when he interrupted me with "First of all, you are going to change your tone!" and he was not talking about the tone level of my voice.
Totally inappropriate (not to say "weird") attitude, to end up saying that we could sit wherever we wanted, contradicting his trainee. Hard to believe that this guy was given some kind of manager or supervisor position.
My mother, being upset with the rudeness of this guy, asked me if we could leave, so this is what we did, without having had breakfast.

The Renaissance was my plan B, in case the Westin was sold to become a luxury hotel. It is no longer my plan and needless to say that I will not return to this property. I'll probably switch to an IHG hotel in case the Westin is sold out.

Too many tiny rooms in that hotel located in a narrow street with a narrow-minded management which does not seem to understand the importance of loyalty (on both ends).
I also noticed an unequal cleaning service and burned my arm on the towel heater that had been set up at the maximum temperature before I checked in - beware of that heater in the small bathroom, if you stay there).
At the end, the responsibility falls with the GM.

I assumed the fact that I am spoiled, but it is only because Starwood, then Marriott have been spoiling me for a long time and I have been trying to be very loyal to them in return (will return to the Ambassador level this year, after a 2-year interruption).

To end on a good note, most of the staff is pleasant, even in the restaurant (in the afternoon, you will see the restaurant staff occupying the adjacent sidewalk during their break, forcing people, some with luggage, to move on the street.

We have done a lot of hotels in Paris but this one was one to remember! From the moment we entered in the room, the staff was already there ready to take our luggage and make us feel comfortable while my husband was doing the check in. The room was magical and I had probably one of the best sleep in my life on that bed. The spa is beautiful and there is even a sauna and hammam. It is kid friendly and everyone feels welcomed.
The breakfast was so delicious and the staff was very friendly, always ready to help and check if everything was going well. You feel extra special and that is thanks to the whole team at Renaissance! Can’t recommend it enough!!

I am a Marriott Ambassador+ member so I have stayed a few nights in hotels and may know a thing or two about them. (hahahaha!)

Our stay at this hotel was fantastic. The location is amazing. Walking distance to the Louvre and amazing shopping were the main reasons we chose this hotel. The clean, beautiful rooms and fantastic service are the reasons we are coming back next time we are in Paris.

Check in was easy and the staff was very professional, polite and spoke/understood English very well. The concierge was able to get us great reservations and gave excellent recommendations for places to explore and eat.

The room was small (as most hotel rooms in Paris are) but it was very nice, the beds were VERY comfortable and clean and the hotel appears in general to be recently renovated. The bathroom was beautiful and VERY clean which is very, very important to me. The amenities in the bathroom were upscale (Le Labo). The towels were actually soft which is unusual. The noise level in our room (412) was better than we expected. We were able to sleep quite well each night.

The breakfast we had was delicious and worth getting.

We will definitely be coming back. Thank you so much for an amazing stay!

Good location and the room was ok. But service isn't impressive! Being called at 0:45 am (in the middle of the night), not answering, then being woken up again because somebody is knocking on the door... it turns out to be a guy from the front desk, wondering if we had got back the wrong suit from dry cleaning. That was that nights deep sleep... But the worst was on the morning of check out. Went to the front desk before breakfast, asking for a taxi to get to the airport half an hour later. When we get there at the agreed time, the guy at the desk just says that he couldn't book any taxi. No help to get, except the question, if we didn't have the Uber App and could order the taxi ourselves... not impressive. And no thank you, we will not return.

Hotel is perfect location. It is located in a quiet area Near Metro and many good restaurants
Staff was amazing! They were very helpful with all of our needs. The breakfast was fabulous each morning. I am a marriott titanium elite and give Vendome my highest ratings. We look forward to returning soon

I am a Marriott platinum member. The location of this hotel is great — lots of what you want within easy walking distance. Everyone working at the hotel was pleasant and very friendly. English seemed like the first language here.

Unfortunately, there were more than a few problems: 1. Our room was tiny. We’ve stayed in small rooms in big cities, but this was the smallest by far; 2. There were literally no drawers in the room to store our clothes — none; 3. The shower is incredibly small. So small it is almost impossible to turn around. 4. To make matters worse, there are two very small shower doors that both have to be open to get in and out. One of our doors was broken and was off the track almost no matter what you did. I went to the front desk to let them know. No repair. Went back next day and the response was that they put it back on track but maybe it couldn’t be repaired. Never got fixed. 5. First day used the glasses in our room. Three days later dirty glasses still there. 6. Asked for ice and a corkscrew on the first day. They arrived in less than ten minutes. Second day asked for ice and wine glasses. Hour and a half later nothing arrived. 7. Room cleaned on third day. Dirty glasses still there and no wash cloths. Back downstairs and asked for wash cloths. Called back and said they had no clean wash cloths. Never got a wash cloth the rest of our stay. They brought more bath towels which took up way too much room with no drawers. 8. Restaurant/ bar is very loud. Some may like that which is fine but there is no where there to have a quiet drink at the end of the day — especially when your room is so small. 9. Workout room is very small — not even enough room to properly stretch. The room requires a separate key but we were not told that when we checked in. So went to basement trying to get in and eventually figured out my room key didn’t work. Upon asking, front desk gives you a key that looks exactly like your room key so very hard to keep separate. After two days that stopped working so down and back again. One of the two elevators goes to the basement. One does not. The one that doesn’t still has a button for the basement. Takes a little while to figure out it doesn’t work. Sometimes there is water in the workout room but sometimes not.

I think the really small size of our room and shower colored our experience. On this trip through Spain and France we stayed at four different Marriott affiliated properties. All of the experiences and rooms were great except this one. We will stay elsewhere next time even though we really liked the location.

Awesome location, right in the heart of the city center and close to all of the major tourist attractions. Lots of luxury shopping and dining right outside your door. Hotel was small, with the main entrance tucked away in what was virtually an alleyway. Service was very good, although our rollaway bed was not set up when we arrived and we had to ask for extra towels. The room was TINY, especially with the extra bed. Fortunately there was extra closet space with shelves, so we had places to tuck our stuff away. The shower was like an RV shower, probably the smallest I've ever seen in a hotel room. I do not understand the concept of the picture on the ceiling. Every morning I would wake up to see this woman watching me! There were virtually no English language TV channels available and the ability to connect my mobile device to stream didn't work. While I would probably consider other options on a future stay, the price was very reasonable for the area.

Overall this was a wonderful stay. Service across the board was fantastic; reception, bell desk, restaurant, housekeeping, everyone was super friendly and helpful. My wife and I were traveling with our 9-month old; the staff came right up to our room and set up the baby crib with great care. For those saying rooms are too small, please remember this is central Paris. The rooms are well sized for the area and designed very smartly. Breakfast is excellent, with a simple but well thought out buffet, your choice of egg dishes and fresh made barista coffee. The hotel takes great care of Bonvoy elites; I am titanium and my Suite Night Award cleared all the way to a Parisian Corner Suite. #507 might be the best room in the property. If you need to stay in the Vendome area, then I highly recommend this property.

Very nice boutique-style hotel in a great location. Minutes to the Lourve. 15 minutes to d'Orsay. The RER C line is across the street from d'Orsay. This runs out to rive gauch (Palace at Versailles). A lot of very good restaurants within a short walk. Everyone we encountered spoke very good English. Both at the Renaissance and at brasseries and cafés. The rooms are typical big city size. The bed and pillows were extremely comfortable.

Flew overnight and on zero sleep. I expected them not to have a room not to be available right away. But, now I’m more than 5 hours in the lobby waiting. Apologies, apologies but no room.
Friendly but incompetent staff!
A waste of this day. Probably will stay elsewhere next time.

Swapped hotels midway through my Paris stay and was impressed with the impeccable hotel right when I entered through the front doors!
Check in staff was super friendly. Lobby area had ample seating.
The bottom floor includes a spa that can be accessed with a separate room key and is included for hotel guests.
I was on the first floor, room was small but normal for a room in Europe. For 2 people, it can be pretty tight. I had a separate shower and bathtub in my room.
My only complaint about this hotel is that you can hear people in the hallway, including the doors opening and closing which was annoying if you were trying to fall asleep.
Breakfast was included for platinum members. Eggs and coffee made to order, buffet included meat and cheese, cold dishes that included egg/potatoes, cauliflower, salad, etc.

Overall as this was my first Renaissance hotel part of Marriott, I would not mind staying here again. I would definitely choose this over the Westin if you’re looking for a Marriott property in Vendome area.

A lovely hotel with a fantastic location! The beds are amazing and plenty of storage space. You can take the metro and walk everywhere. Great restaurants, easy walking to many interesting sights. The hotel restaurant is
lovely Middle Eastern so kind and friendly. I will be back
and loved staying here for six days. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

This property is perfectly located in the heart of Paris. Terrific shopping/restaurants all w/in walking distance. Front desk Mgr Beatriz is a STAR. Jussie (Spain) can do it all...
The breakfast offered the best cooked eggs we ate the past 2 weeks. The lobby is small but I had a lot of fun there.
Room 105 had an on-going bathtub drain issue that never got resolved in our 3 night stay. Housekeeping inconsistent and not up to the Marriott standard of excellence...
This property is well staffed. People are hustling to provide a wow experience. They spend a lot of time training and it shows.
*Recommended...

I invited my mother to join me in Paris to celebrate her 80th birthday - a very special moment if there is one! Her four days stay had to be perfect and I was anxious to make it so, electing the Renaissance for its central location and the quality of its services. It was a winner.

The Renaissance staff was very friendly and professional throughout our stay, everyone going the extra mile to make our stay an unforgettable experience. They played a key role in making our get together a wonderful, memorable one.

The hotel itself is in perfect shape, recently renovated, the room was beautiful and spacious with all amenities, a real treat.
The restaurant and bar are trendy and busy - even if I had no time to try them out!

Location is perfect -you save a lot of time with all sights at a walking distance. Excellent choice for a relaxing, safe and upscale stay!

My family and I enjoyed our stay at this wonderful hotel. This The staff were particularly friendly and helpful, really made us feel comfortable and welcome. Any problem or issue we had was handled perfectly. The breakfast is terrific, too much delicious food! Location is great especially if you like art: very short walk to the Tuileries, l’orangerie, Musée du Louvre, Musée d’Orsay etc. Sad to leave, looking forward to our return. Merci bcp!

You can’t beat the location of this hotel! Right near the Louvre,Tuileries, Rue St Honare. Wonderful welcome,terrific concierge assistance. Restaurant staff very helpful and efficient, lovely breakfast.
Extremely comfortable room with all amenities, it is my first choice always in Paris!

From the moment we arrived we were treated with impeccable service. We flew in and arrived in Paris at 6am and went straight to the hotel (took is 2 hrs to get there with traffic etc). We were not expecting our room to be ready so we had pre-booked massages with the hotel at 10:15- we barely made it on time. The spa is small and not the nicest I have been to, but it is in Paris and the prices were more than reasonable. The massage was great- and they got us out in time for our lunch at the restaurant at the Eiffel Tower.

The breakfast here is also amazing! We stayed 5 nights and I look forward to having the opportunity to go back. We ordered room service twice, and it was delicious. Thank you for an amazing stay, great service, great rooms, great food, good spa! Highly recommend!

Titanium Elite members asked for early check in since we had an overnight flight…got to hotel at 9am. Ventured out into the city waiting for text that our room was ready…never happened. Returned to hotel at 4pm and room still not ready…supposed to ready at 3pm at the latest. We sat at front desk while they “searched” for a room and told us they had an upgrade…from size of room we received and the images online it is the exact same room we booked. To top off the long wait, the room is unfortunately worn and dirty. Does not feel clean. Not happy with this Marriott choice at this time:(

Location, Location, Location! We stayed for 6 nights at this Marriott property and boy; it sure Did Not disappoint. The Place Vendome neighborhood is simply luxurious; this Location was just perfect not too touristy, yet withing walking distance to all the main tourist sites with plenty of Restaurants, Cafes, and Bars around the residential/not so touristy neighborhood and of course the fabulous Luxe shopping all around.
Towards the left forward-facing street of the hotel is the Jardin des Tuileries, Louvre etc. and the rear of the Hotel Place Vendome with all the Luxe shopping and the cafes, bars etc..
The Hotel staff were very friendly, courteous and helpful especially with managing reservations at hard-to-get restaurants or shows. The hotel sports small rooms yet very well appointed with all the usual amenities. We were greeted each evening with thoughtful welcoming surprises; Day 1 our bathroom Basin was filled with ice and a champagne bottle plunged in, with a note “Save water drink Champagne” the next evening a bottle of wine & macaroons from the famous Laudree, Gin and tonics the next, sweet savories from Mado a Paris the next, more wine... and the list endless... Only disappointment was with the house keeper, basic room amenities like coffee, sugar, creamer, coffee/tea disposable cups were not replenished daily same with the case of bathroom amenities like soap shampoo, lotion etc. was not replenished. The Hotels popular Restaurant Balagan was one of my Favorite restaurants on this trip and naturally the Hotels navigator managed to get us a reservation despite it being full the entire week. I have to say staying here in this hotel at this location made all the difference and made my trip memorable. Thank you!

I booked a junior suite and used my suite night upgrades and had a fantastic room. We had two little balcony windows, one in the king bed room and one in the living room area (pull out sofa). The most amazing part of the suite were the TWO bathrooms. This was a game changer for three people.
Service: The hotel was very helpful. I was curious to see how things would be coming out of the pandemic.
Cleanliness: The hotel was very clean. We could request the room to be cleaned up or call for new towels.
Marriott Status: We were offered breakfast in the restaurant. The food was very good and we had free reign of the menu. It did not feel like they were trying to cut corners or limit what you could eat. My friend loved the coffee.
Decor: The hotel was beautiful. The decor was cohesive and the hotel was filled with lovely details. The rooms were up to date and had accessible outlets.
I plan to stay again in a few months.

I debated between the Westin and this property, but the reviews convinced me and I am glad I booked the Renaissance. I appreciated the updated space and rooms. The Westin has the views, but the Renaissance was worth it. We had views of Parisian apartments and rooftops.

Parking: When I stayed it was coming out of COVID so parking was free, I am not sure if the garage is still free. The garage is walking distance in Vendome square around the corner. The parking attendant does not speak English. My parking French does not exist so I had to use google translate. The hotel street is very narrow and there was construction, but I imagine it is complete by now. There are a few parallel spots to unload your bags. The doorman was very helpful.

This hotel was fantastic - great location, nice rooms but the most impressive part of the experience was the service. I was shocked at how terrific it was; and every person with whom I interacted was more impressive than the last. From the Front Desk to the Concierge to the Restaurant, Bar and Spa…they were all great. I am Lifetime Titanium with Marriott and I only mention this to say that I stay in a LOT of hotels across many Marriott brands. The Renaissance Vendome out performed every other property by a mile with their service. Ritz and other Marriott properties would do well to emulate the exceptionalism of this hotel. I will be back and I won’t even consider another property.

The hotel is amazing and every single member of the staff were so helpful. Fabulous location that allows you to walk to the main sites and restaurants bars etc. The spa was great, rooms spotless and lots of space. The hotel went out of their way to make it special for my husband’s 50th. Loved it and will definitely go back next time we’re in Paris.

The staff at the hotel were courteous, and helpful. The Dining bar area Balagan is exceptional, and the hostess, Adele, is a gracious young lady who helped seat us on a very busy night. I would stay here again.

Pros: central location, within 10 min walking distance to Jardin de Tuileres, Louvre, Opera, Galeries Lafayette shopping mall, or Opera. Boutique shops and high end shops close by. Large landmarks (park and Vendome statue) made the area easy to navigate. There is a metro station (Tuileres) near by but we didn't take that. The concierge was very helpful/nice and would call for taxis. Free water bottles if you ask the front desk. We had a two room family suite. Consisted of two separate rooms, each with own locking doors, connected by a hallway, and a third locking door to outside hall. One bedroom had two single beds (could be pushed together to make one large queen) and an ensuite bathroom. The other bedroom had one full size (?) large bed and separate bathroom. Each room had a mini frig, coffee maker, french windows that opened to street. Worked for us 4 ladies. Breakfast was included due to Marriott status & delicious: made to order eggs/omelets, salads, roasted cauliflower, smoked salmon, smoked white fish, apples, oranges, cut fruit, croissant assortment, yogurt, granola, fresh OJ, fresh grapefruit juice, coffee made to order, cold cut meats, cheese assortments, jams, fresh baked cookies,
Cons: If you have a room with a view of the street, it's very loud from people smoking outside the restaurant/bar on 1st floor. They are outside yelling until at least 2-4 AM on a Mon/Tues night. This restaurant/bar is PACKED at night and we had to close the windows due to smoke/pot. I asked for a quiet room, high floor, and with a view. They put me on the 4th floor (high), but only rooms with views are those overlooking the street. The quietest rooms have a view of inner courtyard. I wore earplugs so didn't bother me, but other ladies woke due to noise.

5 nights in January - notwithstanding the pandemic, our stay was completely enjoyable. The hotel has been refurbished and the rooms are relatively large and pleasant. The spa is an unusual bonus for Paris. hotels. We did not have a chance to taste the in-house Balagan restaurant but from the sounds of music emanating from the restaurant and the bar every night, it sounded as if guests were having a very good time. The staff was extremely pleasant and helpful throughout our stay. Being a Platinum Bonvoy member I was treated accordingly and received all amenities as expected.

Lovely stay at the Renaissance Vendome hotel! The staff is really friendly and interested in you! A special thank for Mattia, Jussi and the entire team to make it a wonderul experience! It was a present for my girlfriend and we were spoiled with a bottle of champagne and an upgrade for the room!

Marriott quality with wonderful service. This hotel had excellent service and is in a fantastic location - everywhere is easy to walk to - not necessarily the easiest to get in and out by car though with the traffic. The hotel porter (what looked like the youngest) was fantastic - always attentive and even flagged a yellow cab on the streets for me when none could be booked to get to the airport. The hotel treated me with such respect and I had such a lovely time here. Breakfast was incredibly delightful as well - fresh cheese and yummy croissants. I did book a suite and it was a massive room decorated beautifully - the bathrooms are still a bit small, but it's to be expected in a central European big city. There is noise from the restaurant into late hours on the weekends as I think a lot of people will go to the restaurant bar downstairs, but close the curtains and the sound muffles and I was able to sleep wonderfully. I only wish I could have stayed at the hotel longer!

Title: Excellent service. Perfect location for tourists.

Pro: Up close and personal service, perfect location for tourists, good buffet breakfast, excellent bed

Con: Nothing major to complain about. Broken USB ports on my side of the bed?

When most staff addressed me when I walked in and out of the hotel, I knew I came to the right place. "Good morning Mr Lam", "Good afternoon Mr Lam. How was your day?", "Good evening Mr Lam. Is there anything I can help you with?" It almost felt like butler service. Thanks to Tunde, Aude, Thomas, Slim, Nixon, and other staff I didn't get a chance to know their names for doing a great job during my stay, and also to Beatriz for making all this happen. This is one well managed hotel.

Location wise, it is best for tourists who want the convenience to get to most places by foot or by metro. It is right between Jardin des Tuileries and Place Vendome. Louvre? 5 mins. Brand name shopping? 5 mins. Tuileries and Concorde metro stations, 5 mins. Angelina? Parisian cafes? They are everywhere around the hotel. I can't describe in detail how conveniently located this hotel is. We walked to the the Eiffel Tower and to Arc de Triomphe by foot from the hotel.

The Cal King bed was super. I slept like a pig during my stay.

Special mention to Slim for making my daughter super happy, and to Thomas for suggesting an excellent place for escargot. My wife and daughter were very satisfied with the recommendations.

All in all, I picked the right place to celebrate my wedding anniversary.

Shortcomings? Well, USB ports on my side of the bed (window side) were broken. The SmartTV had problems with its Chromecast. I couldn't get YouTube to work on it. Marriott has standardized customer experience with their smart TV's but this one just didn't work. Some people complained about noise around the hotel. Well, you can't have this much convenience if you don't stay in a busy area. Right? The desk... it is good for light-duty work. If someone wants to put several laptops on the desk to day trade, the desk won't work.

As a Titanium Elite and a lifetime member of the Bonvoy program, I have stayed at many different hotels within the chain, year after year. For a Cat 7 hotel, I would say this one exceeds the experience I had with other Marriot Cat 7 hotels I visited this year. Ritz Carlton definitely did not give me this level of service and satisfaction. Maybe someone from Marriott needs to do a case study?

Once again, thank you to the hotel staff for making my wedding anniversary special.

We will be back!

Belagan, the hotel's contracted restaurant and bar, attracts the wrong kind of clientele.

I saw two male customers doing crack cocaine in the hotel men's toilet, which is shared with the restaurant. This was reported to the front desk, which told me I should complain to the restaurant. Maybe my complaint was lost in translation (I speak English) but the bathroom is run by the hotel not the restaurant.

Who wants to stay in a hotel where guests are openly doing illicit drugs?

At night, the hotel should have an attendant work the bathroom to keep it clean and monitor customer activity.

We just returned from an incredible 4 night stay at the Renaissance Vendome. The hotel is in the perfect location for walking to top attractions The staff was helpful, and went out of their way to ensure we had everything we needed for an enjoyable stay. Special shout out to the concierge team. Without them, I would have been lost! The front desk staff as well was always ready to offer a bottle of water or answer any questions. The bar just off the lobby was an added pleasant surprise. The staff there is truly passionate about their food and drinks. In short- I was glad we selected this hotel for our special vacation. There are many to select from, and I chose wisely.

This is NOT a 5-star hotel and more like a motel. The bathrooms
are not clean nor functional. There are no toiletries as in true 5-
star hotels and you must ask for towels. (Really 1 washcloth for
2 adults and 1 large towel and 2 hand towels) There are MANY
hotels in the area at the same price offering much better
accommodations. You just won't get your Bonvoy points. We
do NOT choose hotels based upon loyalty points / rewards. We
did choose this hotel as it was described and portrayed by
Marriott.
More disappointing is the lack of service and responsiveness to
try to resolve. As mentioned in the letter to Marriott, we
decided to tough it out as it was too difficult to relocate to
another property. As many times as we complained about
noise,(construction on the street and the bar/pub noise from
below inside the hotel) service, and the cleanliness / amenities,
nothing was done.
This is “bait and switch” at its best and false advertising as to
the type of property it truly is. Shame on Marriott for this
behavior.
Most definitely feel used, abused and overcharged… NOT worth
the value proposition / experience.

I stayed here for 10 nights on a recent business trip. The desk they provide is too small to work at, and the in-room chair is a bongo-looking wooden stool. There is no overhead light by which to read, and the hotel has no extra lamps to provide. Rue Thabor is incredibly loud, with people yelling in the street until 10pm. There is also a building renovation happening directly across the hotel, so construction begins at 7am and deliveries of materials can occur until 11pm. Room service menu is very limited to the adjoining restaurant and quite expensive (25-40 euro/dish). The staff mean well but are under-trained. I had one employee try to come into my room at 10:30 at night for an unknown reason, and after the chain lock blocked him, he persisted to ring the bell until he woke me up and I answered the door. He was apparently looking to collect some kind of trash? 90% of the people that I saw here were foreign tourists on a day or two jaunt in Paris. For that, the location is very good, and you probably won't be bothered by the way the place operates. For a business traveler, I'd strongly avoid.

Just returned from a 4 night stay at the Renaissance Vendome. The hotel is very clean and in an upscale location of Paris. However - the friendliness of the staff is what really made our trip. Elsa the concierge answered our many questions about tickets, boat rides, restaurants and covid testing and helped with all the arrangements. Jussi the bellman was ready every morning to bring us a coffee with a smile. Thank you for a wonderful stay!

Overall I am not impressed.

Bed very comfortable and friendly staff.

Loud music plays all night from the bar, even during the week. I arrived on a Thursday and was unable to fall asleep with heavy bass playing until beyond 1:30am.

Breakfast limited and not very nice. Croissants and pain au chocolat are not fresh, I didn’t eat them. But nice lattes.

The ‘fitness centre’ is an OLD multipurpose apparatus with a yoga mat on the floor for stretching. The ‘free weights’ are dumbbells and only going up to 10kg.

Arrived Thursday and the spa treatments were already fully booked until Monday.

I stay with Marriotts as a member with Chairman status and the benefits of this hotel do not match others in the group. A sad packet of nuts waiting on arrival (but at least an OK bottle of red also waiting).

I visit Paris several times a year but it is unlikely that I will be returning to this hotel.

Modern, upscale hotel with a welcoming staff and nicely done rooms. Had a junior suite with small sitting area and nepresso for morning coffee. Bathroom small but modern. Location near the Tulleries and the Louvre.Upscale shoping surrounds.

THE HOTEL STAFF IS EXCEPTIONAL & brings us back again & again.

1 - THE STAFF
People make the difference here at the Renaissance Paris Vendome Hotel. The front desk staff is friendly, welcoming, accommodating. The breakfast room staff (including a lovely woman named Adele) went way way way above & beyond in making us feel like guests in their own home. Friendly, attentive, helpful, and the energy they projected to accommodate us was a joy and especially appreciated by me - someone who becaues of global pandemic have not traveled in 17 months. Example: One evening we were too tired to leave for dinner, but hungry. Unable to get a seat in restaurant without reservation, and room too small to eat comfortably- the staff welcomed us to order room service but eat in the lobby. Brilliant idea, they went out of their way to think about how to solve for us and make it a great experience. Can't tell you how much we love the spirit of your team!

2- THE FOOD
Breakfast every morning was excellent, with a daily salad changing each day. Loved the choice of oatmeal, eggs, salads, fruits and breads. A limited room service menu - (but the good news is that food quality is HIGH - because it is connected to a dynamite restaurant downstairs)

3-THE ROOM
Super comfortable room - not too spacious. Coffee maker and fridge in room. Furniture, the room all in good condition - and the cleaning staff did a super job!

4-THE LOCATION.
Fabulous location - Paris is of course a great walking city, but for us virtually everything is walking distance, and we love this as a base. Steps away from the Seine, the Louvre, the gardens.

The team every before we travelled there has been amazing to help us plan. The responsiveness and problem solving is of a different order. Cant thank them enough especially Solange. She has tried to address every problem we have come up with. Amazing

This hotel has truly amazing service from check in to every time you need anything, every time you walk through the lobby, every time you need the concierge to book something, the service is impeccable. The restaurant is wonderful. The people in the restaurant are wonderful. Truly a five star service experience with a beautiful quiet hotel. Very comfortable rooms with excellent climate control. The location cannot be beat with the Louvre, the Musée d'Orsay, the Tuileries Garden, and the Musée de l'Orangerie within walking distance.

As a Marriott Platinum member, I obviously frequent Marriott Hotels worldwide. This Marriott exceeded expectations via customer service and location!
Loved everything about it and will certainly stay again!
The restaurant was excellent too!

I have stayed a few nights at the Paris Vendome Renaissance hotel a few weeks back.
I have to say this was one of the most disappointing stays at a Marriott or Renaissance hotels in decades. Below my feedback on the several incidents:
1/ Staff training: it is so obvious that the majority of your staff at the checking, room service and restaurant are ill trained. A couple of agents at the checkin were extremely professional and knew what they were doing. The rest were at loss: ordering a taxo too 30mns. Getting into my room: 45mns. Printing a document: delays since there is no business center.
2/ Cleanliness: while awaiting for my room at the reception area, customers couldd smell sewage odors. The same odor remained in the elevators for days.
3/ most importantly: I was very disappointed with the quality of service at the restaurant. I have attended the restaurant for breakfast for 3 days: systematically my orders weren't taken accurately. I literally had to wait for 40 mins to get a cafe latte and a croissant while the restaurant had barely 3 tables being taken care of. On my first attendance, I thought I got unlucky and the person attending me wasn't fast enough. On the subsequent days, different staff members inclusive of the manager behaved with he same disregard. The staff was not organized, the kitchen slow, totally unacceptable for a hotel of this level or for the prices we pay at this establishment.
I cannot stress enough how disorganized the staff was and how ill trained they were. I honestly have never ever experienced such poor quality of service in 50+ Marriott hotels I've attended worldwide.
For 500 euros a night, one can expect a minimum of attention and quality of service.
4/ Rooms: the rooms are tiny (even by Parisian rooms standards). The minibar was empty and the staff didn't even present the offers to fill it in.

Fabulous neighborhood. Close to many cafes and shopping and very walkable area, but not on a main thoroughfare. Staff was very accommodating, and was able to get us into our rooms many hours before normal check in. Very welcome after a long night of travel. We did alert them ahead of our early arrival, which I would recommend. The only negative was we reserved rooms with a balcony and rooftop views, but with major construction right across a small street, these were unusable during the day. We were not notified of this prior. But as most visitors are out all day, this may not be a problem. The windows are double paned so the rooms were very quiet at night. The breakfasts were fantastic, as were all the staff we encountered. Overall a very nice stay.

Amazing hotel in the very center of Paris, in a clean and safe neighbourhood. If you want to discover the city, this is the place to be.
I was actually impressed how well the COVID-19 measurements taken by Marriott worked.
The staff was also very friendly. Happy I have stayed there 👌🏼

This was my first stay. A wonderful location right in the center when visiting Paris. The hotel is situated on a ultra quiet street in the heart of the oldest parts of Paris.
The hotel was in easy walking distance of many tourist attractions and had great luxury shops near by.
The staff is extremely friendly, pleasant, accommodating, and well-informed about the neighborhood and Paris in general, thanks to Lisa and Emeline.
The room was comfortable, well-appointed and clean, the wifi is very good to get some work done.
I am already planning for my return trip in Paris and I will certainly return to Renaissance Paris Vendôme.
Thank you guys et Joyeux Noël

Service is nothing special, with all limitations implemented due to COVID. No Room Service (Uber Eats), room ok but one can feel and see signs of usage (crack in the sink, marks on the furniture...), breakfast selection ok (just ok) on paper, but it never came according to what I had asked, they would always forget something...
They didn’t ask if and at when would I like to have the room cleaned, so I forgot to mention and realized it when coming back...
At the end, it’s too expensive for the service they are providing!

We stayed here for 5 nights and found that it was in the best location possible for all the attractions we wanted to do. The hotel was very clean and like most Marriott hotels I have stayed at very comfortable. The front desk were very helpful whenever we called down or asked for assistance getting cabs etc. Only down side was the laundry service was expensive and we had just come off a cruise and needed to do some laundry so we ended up hiking 6 blocks to find a laundry facility but it was a good way to see the other side of Paris. The hotel pool and fitness area were spotless and well taken care of.

We stayed in this lovely hotel for three nights.Our room was on the second floor with the courtyard view,so it was very quiet at night.The room wasn't very big but absolutely lovely and cozy with comfortable beds and all modern conveniences. Most of all we were impressed by breakfast.It was really GREAT ! A great variety of cheese,bacon,ham,sausages,fruit,vegetables,dairy,pastry,fresh juice ,omelet(specially cooked for you with any filler) and lots of other delicious things. The hotel is perfectly located just a 5 minute walk to the Louvre and The Tuileries Gardens and 10 minute walk to the Opera,D'Orsey museum and other places of interests. Practically, you don"t have to use public transport to see the main attractions, Just walk and enjoy the city! The staff were very friendly and caring. I'd like to say THANK YOU to the staff and all the waiters ,especially to Tamara who was very nice and helpful when serving the breakfast.

We have just returned from a weekend in Paris staying in this hotel.

From the moment we arrived, the staff were so helpful and we loved every second we stayed. The location is brilliant too. a 4/5min walk to the Louvre and 3min walk to the Tuileries metro station

We met Mattia who cheked us in and then took us to our room - he was exceptionally helpful and informative and made sure the room was to our satisfaction (it was!)

We used the pool which has a very serene feel to it - again the staff were super helpful.

I have no hesitation in recommending this hotel and will definitely return here on our next visit to Paris.

Thank you for making our stay in Paris so enjoyable.

Showed up at the hotel to check into a room that was suppossedly a suite for a relaxing weekend. Far from it. The room had no heating upon check-in. Despite promises to fix it, it never was done. At 2am when arriving back to the hotel, rather than them finding a solution to a problem that they know they did not fix, it was left to us! Had to call the front desk again, explain the problem for the 3rd time and be offered a casual offer to move the room... at 2am!!!! The last thing you want on a restful stay and being tired. Rather than proactively offering any concession at check-out, I was left to calling and hoping to get my points back for a miserable stay!
Despite all the plesantries their "policy" is only to refund a certain amount of points per night which is only 1/2 of what it cost. Policy at Marriott is fix problems and make your custromers happy as I have been for the past 30 years! Not give "Policy" advice. 10 years ago, you could brag and trade on your great location. These days, peple want more than smiles and rejection when dealing with problems. They want genuine understanding that you failed to provide the service you claim to offer. Without it, you lose a customer for a lifetime and get slammed on TripAdvisor. Hopefully the next person will read this and take caution.

p.s. Save the "We value your opionion" canned response to this complaint. If you understand cutomer service you will do what is right. Refund the full points.

Book a junior suite in this lovely hotel and you will enjoy it even more. The rooms are small but cute and tastefully furnished. Breakfast was superb and ample. Location … well its near everything , walking distance, more or less. I would stay here again!!!

This is a very good hotel in a fantastic location. If you are touring the major sights of Paris you can walk to them all, especially the Louvre or Tuileries. The rooms are small but functional and the staff is very helpful. If i had to quibble about anything it would be to open the small but cozy bar a little sooner.

We had a great stay at this hotel.Very good location near Louvre ,very clean and with a cozy restaubar inside.Helpful staff nice and modern room but small and a little bit pricey. All in all was a great stay.

Wonderful experince and great location close to Rue St Honree and the Louvre. My room was very clean and nicely appointed. The breakfast at Balagan was fantastic and so was the service. We were greeted warmly by reception. Maximillian, the door man went the extra mile to walk my wife to the train station as she needed help to navigate during the strike. Under normal circumstances the metro is a few steps away and easy to use. Thanks again for a great experience!

Friendly and accommodating staff. We stayed in the "Prestige, Larger Guest room" with a King sized bed and it was comfortable. Although the room was not what one might consider large, it was of decent size.

Location-wise, it's about a block or so from Jardin des Tuileries, the Louvre, the Seine and EXCELLENT shopping. The husband and I had been to Paris several times before but we decided to book Paris to do some sight seeing with my 3.5 year old as she developed a bit of a Paris obsession (Madeline books, images of Eiffel Tower etc) and had a great experience here.

Upon arrival, there was a hand written note to welcome us, complimentary bottle of wine, an Evian, chocolates and some cheese biscuits waiting for us which was a nice touch. Margiela toiletries was also a plus.

Hours after check out, I'd received an email invoice reflecting some discrepancies with the minibar purchases. We called and they took care of it immediately.

We stayed here on our first trip to Europe and enjoyed every day. The hotel staff was polite and helpful and the rooms were first rate. We took advantage of the on site restaurant for breakfast (a Mediterranean mix) with our last night with reservations to an incredible meal and wine. With a short walk to the Tuileries, everything we wanted to see was accessible from there. We hope to go back again.

Boutique hotel offering great rooms, service, and location! The central location allows for easy walks to many of the top sites of Paris. I used Marriott Rewards points and they gave me an upgrade. 😀😀😀😀😀

I have been a customer of Marriott for over 10 years. My recent experience at Marriott Renaissance Paris Vendome over the Thanksgiving Holiday started to great an ended terribly. Upon my departure I was burned by a heated towel rack the had no indicator of being on. I bought this to the attention of the staff immediately and I was given first aid. However, the aftermath of this incident was less than desirable. Since the incident occurred, no one has from Marriott has contacted me to remedy this situation and I've constantly gotten the run around from everyone at the hotel and corporate headquarters. I've also spoken with Marriott's Consumer affairs department Still no resolution to date, Marriott customers Beware!

My husband and I recently stayed at the Renaissance Paris Vendome and it was fantastic. It's a lovely boutique-like hotel in a great location. Considering the strikes that have been going on in Paris, we knew that we wouldn't be utilizing public transportation once we arrived in the city. This hotel was perfect for walking to a lot of museums and was about two blocks from the Christmas Market in the Tuileries. We also walked to the Eiffel Tower (albeit it was a longer walk). The rooms were nice and clean, although they were a little on the smaller side, which is perfectly fine for us. The service was exceptional and we would definitely stay at this hotel again.

Lovely Renaissance property with a boutique feel. Does not feel at all like a cookie cutter Marriott. Property is in a heavily travelled neighborhood, yet it is tucked away on a rather secluded side street.

Room: Rooms are average sized, very clean and efficiently styled. We had a 2 BR suite which was 2 rooms connected by a hallway. There was no living area. Beds were super comfortable. Bathrooms were spotless, though due to the lack of a door or shower curtain - there was only a half glass panel. The floor got really wet anytime the kids took a shower.

Location: Walking distance to high end shopping and the Vendôme area. The Louvre and Musée D;Orsay were both within 10 minute walks. There was a large holiday festival a block away that was rather touristy. Neighborhood was safe, though there was some rather rambunctious street noise in the late hours.

Service: Staff were pleasant and professional. I was a little irritated that i had requested a rollaway bed and had called a week before to confirm. When I arrived, i was informed that there were no rollaways available, which left me with no alternative than to book a expensive third room. Then I when i checked out, they attempted to charge me for the rollaway anyway. The front desk person removed it once I pointed it out. In hindsight, the smallish 2 BR "suite" really did not leave enough room for a rollaway, but i wish they had told me this ahead of time. The whole situation was really messy.

Food: Breakfast was in the restaurant adjacent to the lobby, and offered various pastries, cheeses and fruit, as well as eggs and omelette.

Other: The hotel gave us a nice welcome package with a few bottles of wine, some cookies and chocolates. There were snacks and hot chocolate served in the lobby each night.

We had a corner suite for two nights and it was delightful.
A comfortable bed and a quiet restful sleep are imperative when you are out running around all day. Management accommodated our request for an early check-in.
When in Paris, we'll definitely stay here again.
Merci!

My family visited Paris over Thanksgiving. We would never stay at the Renaissance Vendome again. This tiny hotel has a nightclub off of their lobby that plays high bass, high volume music until 2 am. The hotel deemed it appropriate to place hotel rooms on the floor right above the nightclub. We were the lucky guests to be given two of those rooms. The hotel was fully booked so there was nowhere to move us and so we suffered for two nights with the nightclub pumping away below us. Our children could not sleep until 2 am when the music and shouts and loud singing finally stopped. I am appalled that the hotel would even consider this appropriate.

Otherwise, the rooms were small but we were expecting that, given the hotel's size and location. As to housekeeping, we did not have any issues except that it was disturbing that there is no top sheet under the duvet. I wonder whether (and hope) they change the duvet after each guest, but I doubt it. The breakfast was fine, although it had a Mediterranean bent that wasn't our preference and so we only ate there once. There are a number of great breakfast places close by, though, so we certainly didn't starve.

Location is great but you have a huge selection of hotels around and we will be selecting one of the other hotels in the future.

This was our second stay at this hotel and we enjoyed our stay. The hotel underwent renovation recently and it is more stylish, The staff is welcoming, pleasant, and very helpful .
Enjoyed the breakfast daily in the downstairs cafe. The food was good and the waitstaff helpful.
The bedroom was small but clean and comfortable and quiet, The bathroom was larger than most and again clean. The only negatives about the room were that the bed could use a new mattress and there was a very large picture above the bed. It was a picture of a girl wearing sunglasses staring down at you, This was a little odd,
Overall, the best part of this hotel is still the location. You can walk to many major attractions and it is in a lovely neighborhood,
I would choose to stay at the Renaissance Paris Vendome hotel again.

My husband and I stayed at the Renaissance Paris Vendome for 4 nights in mid November, traveling with two friends. We had read the reviews warning of the small rooms, but we rechecked the website which says the Paris rooftop rooms are on the 5th floor and are 22sq./m or 237 sq feet—not too bad. The picture shows a spacious room with two windows and after living in a tiny NYC apartment for over 20 years, we felt this was a non-issue. Our friends checked in first for a booking identical to ours. Their room is just as pictured on the Marriott.com website. However, when we checked-in, there was only one window, a much smaller room than pictured, 30% smaller than our friends. The room was so small, that if the curtain was closed you had to physically move the fabrics to get into and out of bed. On the other side of the bed, only one person can access the closet at a time.

Besides the small room that was less than promised, the water temperature in the shower would fluctuate so badly that you’d be either chilled or scalded. The front desk said they sent someone to look at it, day after day that we complained, but it persisted throughout our stay.

After filling out the survey upon our return home, the management sent an email assuring us the room we stayed in was the one we booked. The pictures and dimensions on the website prove this to be incorrect. Nicolas also said he offered us a different room but we declined. The truth is he offered to UPSELL us a more expensive room. Having decided this place was not going to get another dime, we declined.

The doormen are great, very helpful at finding our Uber, hailing taxis, and opening doors. The room was kept clean by prompt housekeeping service, though turndown service went 2 of 4 nights. Beds were very comfortable though there was no top sheet, just a duvet. The location is terrific, but definitely not worth the money or layers of skin lost in the scalding shower.

This is not a 5 star hotel. The rooms are not as described. I’d suggest staying somewhere else.

the location of the hotel is super central: near the faubourg st honore and 5 lin walkjng distance from Le Louvre museum. The rooms are ‘ok’: a bit small, nice bed, efficient design, but the main disappointment for a 5 star hotel comes from the bathroom: it looks like more a one star hotel...The service was good overall. The restaurant was also a big disappointment: food was very basic...and the staff not up to the level of a 5 star hotel...more at the level of a basic neighborhood restaurant...last but not least...the lobby had no ‘identity’: cold and lack of charm...

The hotel has a excellent location and courteous staff . It’s located in the best neighborhood of Paris - walking distance from Tuileries Garden , Louvre, Concorde . The decor is nice and the rooms are small ( petites) with difficulty to storing the luggage and hanging clothes . A petite cafe for morning breakfast with a generous spread but little walkable space . It has a small gym which is well equipped and has a steam and sauna room also.
