At the back of the gym is a small swimming pool which is a surprise . For free WiFi you need to have Marriott membership . They have a turndown service every evening . The room amenities include everything that you need .

Just stayed here over thanksgiving. Location is fantastic and staff is nice enough- but there are many issues with this place in terms of general upkeep and amenities. First I am Starwood/Marriott platinum and used my suite upgrade. This hotel doesn’t have a true suite as it’s just a big room with a small sitting area - not even a couch. The second thing —and this is really bad is that housekeeping was absolutely terrible - as in they would skip it sometimes and do things like hang up towels we had put on the floor and not refill our toiletries. The bathroom was also tiny for a suite. They also got our wake up call time wrong and woke us up at 5 am instead of 7 am. I have no idea how this is a 5 star hotel and I’ve stayed at other hotels in Paris- service is always french but rarely are the basics so off. Strongly prefer almost every other hotel I’ve stayed at in Paris.

Very interesting hotel located centrally within walking distance to shopping, the Tuileries Garden, the Louvre and Musee de orsay.

The room is very much on the small side but tastefully decorated, amply appointed, and gives off a vibe of old world glamour.

I was also greeted with a bottle of wine and chocolate and cookies in the room. Nice touch.

Given the size of the room, I would not recommend it for any family with kids.

No US compatible wall sockets, but you can borrow an adapter from the reception desk.

Very friendly staff.

We visited this delightful hotel to celebrate my wife's birthday and stayed for one night.

This hotel has recently been completely renovated and is truly understated elegance. The rooms are tastefully appointed and the beds are super comfy. The location is very convenient with most attractions within a 10-20 minute walk. For the rest, Uber was very easy to use.

The staff could not have been more helpful addressing every single one of our needs with speed and class. We were greeted with champagne, balloons and cake in the room - such a beautiful, unexpected surprise.

Perhaps the only downside was the spa being so busy but this was our fault for not booking in advance.

This is a hotel we would most definitely return to and would not hesitate to recommend.

I am an Ambassador member of Marriot. I came here with my wife for three nights after a business trip in London. The hotel rooms at best are like a Holiday Inn Express with Ikea furniture dated the 1980s. Furniture, room size, and bathrooms are basic. Having been in Paris before there are far better rooms for the same price. Stay somewhere else...

The Renaissance is one of those boutique hotels that Paris does so well, however this hotel is off the scale for position and luxury. Charming staff (lots of them) who cannot do enough to help. Great breakfasts and a dedicated gourmet restaurant. So central, positioned between St Honore and Rivoli, five minutes from the Tuleries and ten from the Louvre. Epic location.

Being a titanium elite member, we got a bottle of wine as a welcome gift and free breakfast. Breakfast buffet contained a variety of tasty items and was a really nice benefit. Made to order omelets and fresh orange juice started the day off right. The room on level 1 was clean but the noise level was high. Friday thru Sunday the street noise from 10:00 PM to 2:00 AM was loud and made sleeping difficult. Started using ear plugs. Staff was friendly and the hotel is located in a great spot.

We have SPG/Marriott Points so we opt to stay at these hotel chains. This location was located in a great part of Paris, very convenient to nearby restaurants and amenities. They accommodated early check-in and the staff was very courteous and helpful. The room itself was very nice for downtown Paris. We would recommend this hotel.

I used 3 of my Suite Nights and got a room that is barely larger than a standard room. I guess boutique means, we have tiny rooms. It is Paris and likely that building is very old too. The location was great though very accessible to lots of the Sights in walking distance. Took Metro to Mont Matre and Boat to the Eiffel Tower. Four Stars only because the restaurant that serves the Breakfast is a mess! Pour Service and very unorganized!

Usually don't like the major chains when traveling in Europe, but this was an excellent property in the heart of Paris. Excellent location for walking all of Paris and the feel of a boutique hotel. They've done a nice job of modernizing an older building, and the rooms are very comfortable and quiet. Great breakfast and the restaurant is currently very hot for dining in Paris. We didn't book ahead and couldn't get in, so would be worth planning ahead. Very attentive service and they provided some thoughtful and much appreciated treats for my birthday. Highly recommend for value, location and quality in Paris.
